g.text: UML Diagram: Class CodeList in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― CodeListStructure: Relation structure of codes within a codelist.
a.xlink:title: ― CodeListStructure: Relation structure of codes within a codelist.

a.title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.

a.title: ― DimensionalKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a dimensional key.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a dimensional key.

a.title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)
a.xlink:title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)

a.title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.
a.xlink:title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.

a.title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).
a.xlink:title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).

a.title: ― LevelStructure: Nesting structure of a hierarchical collection.
a.xlink:title: ― LevelStructure: Nesting structure of a hierarchical collection.

a.title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.

a.title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.
a.xlink:title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
a.xlink:title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― isDefinedBy: The conceptual basis for the collection of members.
a.xlink:title: ― isDefinedBy: The conceptual basis for the collection of members.

a.title: ― references: Category set associated with the enumeration.
a.xlink:title: ― references: Category set associated with the enumeration.

a.title: ― uses: Has meaningful level to which members belong.
a.xlink:title: ― uses: Has meaningful level to which members belong.
